# Link File v1.1
# A collection of Quotes, Lines, and Facts

"The only limit to our realization of tomorrow is our doubts of today." - Franklin D. Roosevelt
"Do what you can, with what you have, where you are." - Theodore Roosevelt
"Success is not final, failure is not fatal: it is the courage to continue that counts." - Winston Churchill
"Life is 10% what happens to us and 90% how we react to it." - Charles R. Swindoll
"The way to get started is to quit talking and begin doing." - Walt Disney
"Whether you think you can, or you think you can't – you're right." - Henry Ford
"Not everything that is faced can be changed, but nothing can be changed until it is faced." - James Baldwin
"Opportunities don't happen. You create them." - Chris Grosser
"It does not matter how slowly you go as long as you do not stop." - Confucius

# Fun Facts
Honey never spoils. Pots of honey have been found in ancient Egyptian tombs over 3,000 years old.
A day on Venus is longer than a year on Venus.
Octopuses have three hearts and blue blood.
Bananas are berries, but strawberries aren’t.
Water can boil and freeze at the same time – it's called the triple point.
The Eiffel Tower can grow 15 cm taller in summer due to heat expansion.
There are more stars in the universe than grains of sand on all Earth’s beaches.

